[h1] Paragraphs

[h2] Inline form

[p] Short text on a single line:

[code-]
[p] This is a short paragraph.
[-code]

[h2] Block form

[p] Longer text that spans multiple source lines:

[code-]
[p-]
This paragraph can span
as many lines as you like.
The browser joins them into one wrapped block of text.
[-p]
[-code]

[h2] align

[p] All paragraph tags support align= with values left (default), center, or right:

[code-]
[p align=center] This line is centered.
[p align=right]  This line is right-aligned.

[p- align=center]
Each wrapped line of this paragraph
will be centered independently.
[-p]
[-code]

[h2] Inline links

[p] Embed a link inside paragraph text with link- ... -link:

[code-]
[p] Visit the [link- file=about.podweb]about page[-link] for details.
[p] Go to [link- user=12345]this user[-link] or back to [link- file=index.podweb]home[-link].
[p] Open [link- url="https://example.com/page.podweb"]an external page[-link] too.
[-code]

[p-]
All the same attributes as standalone links work here: file=, user=, url="...", cart=.
Inline links are highlighted and underlined. They wrap across lines correctly
inside multi-line [p-] blocks too.
[-p]

[h2] Inline downloads

[p] Embed a download button inside a paragraph:

[code-]
[p] Get started by [download url=podnet://YOUR_ID/starter.txt] and follow the guide.
[-code]

[h2] align with inline content

[p-]
When a paragraph contains inline links or downloads, the entire rendered
line is treated as one unit for alignment. The paragraph's align is applied
to the whole line. Any align property on an inline element is ignored.
[-p]

[code-]
[p align=center] See [link- file=about.podweb]the about page[-link] for details.
[-code]

[h2] font

[code-]
[p font=fancy] Short paragraph in a custom font.
[p- font=fancy]
Multi-line paragraph
in a custom font.
[-p]
[-code]

[p] See [link- file=how-to/font.podweb]the font page[-link] for how to declare custom fonts.

[h2] color

[p] Set the text color of a paragraph with color= (a Picotron palette number):

[code-]
[p color=0] This text is black.
[p- color=5]
This whole block renders in dark grey.
[-p]
[-code]

[p-]
The color= on a paragraph affects plain text only. Inline links inside it
always use the link color from the theme or their own color= attribute -
the paragraph color has no influence on them.
[-p]

[p] See [link- file=how-to/colors.podweb]the colors page[-link] for the full theming reference.

